e ground experience panelists tackled central issues and engaged in spirited debate animated by moderator phil taubman the promise of information and communications technology examined whether technology can transform lives of individuals even in poorly governed countries finding encouraging evidence in health and economic development the promise of information and communications technology april 19 2010 special event philip taubman megan smith jared cohen joshua cohen download from the event video video welcome by prof stephen krasner panel 1 the promise of information and communications technology streaming flash video audio audio welcome by prof stephen krasner panel 1 the promise of information and communications technology streaming mp3 search pgj news of interest chris spence enabling moments of opportunity in closed societies using technology september 30 2010 pgj program on liberation technology in the news matt harrison on mobile technology and the evolution of the nation state november 11 2010 pgj program on liberation technology in the news fsi's technology governance and global development conference may 3 2010 fsi stanford news program on global justice just supply chains liberation technology and human rights september 23 2008 fsi stanford cddrl fse news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 724 3241 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
